title: Smart Polymers and their Applications
description:
Smart Polymers and their Applications (Elsevier-WP, 2014).pdf

ISBN 978-0-85709-695-1

Smart polymers are polymers that respond to different stimuli or changes in the environment. The first part of this book reviews the different types of smart polymers, discussing their properties, structure, design and characterization. Part two reviews applications of these materials in areas such as biomedical engineering, textiles, and food packaging, and data storage
